column5: Has anyone noticed that Lake of the Woods and lots of other places are all blurred out on Google Earth. Didn't used to be like that. It's only the water. You can see land near the lake just fine. Anyone else notice this about their favorite lake and if so anyone no why? 4 days 2 hours 25 minutes Thanks, Brett
hi, I noticed that also.maybe its either clouds or morning fog.if in winter months maybe ice.
I looked at that too. I saw some ares where there was clearly ice on the lakes, but that blur rinses looks like silt laden runoff to me.Frank

Looks like fog hanging over the water when the satellite took the photo. Don't think it was ice with all the green in the surrounding land areas. Wish they would update the photo, we will be fishing this area in September.
From my experience, it seems a lot of the area up here is not clearly defined unless it is near a city.

Photos are updated every few years or so. some photos better than others. Photos of the East end of Rainy lake updated last May are so clear you can see the boats at the dock and many small features. half way down the lake the resolution is not as good . Pics are older and have not been updated.
